Bath Ave., north side, between Bay 19th and [Bay] 22nd Streets. A view of the Bensonhurst station of the Brooklyn Bath and West End R.R. The two homes at the right, face 19th Ave; the home in the back right, seen between the two homes, faces Bay 22nd Street. In the background, is Benson Ave.

1888.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(1)
1815-1839 Bath Ave., north side, between Bay 19th and 20th Streets. A view of the B.M.T. Lines, formerly Gunther's Railroad.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
Same, showing fully No. 1839 at right, which is only partially seen in view No. 1. It was once known as the Atlantic Hotel.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Bath Ave., north side, east from Bay 19th Street. No. 1825 is at left foreground.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(1)
144-156 Bay 19th Street, west side, from and including Bath, to but not including Benson Aves. Also seen is Nos. 1805-1819 Bath Ave. from the N.E. corner of Bay 19th to, but not including Bay 18th Streets. All the houses are frame.

February 3, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, a close up also showing Coney Island Car coming into Bath Ave. Also Shown are frame houses.

February 3, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.
